{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Authentication-Flow","text":"Authentication Flow"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":", which contained the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:"}]},{"code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here are the changes being made:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters: now, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is responsible.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer stored inside of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"text":": now, a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"UUID","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" value has been added to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" now closely follows ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", but have moved to default implementations of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A new ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"`SessionConfiguration`","level":2,"anchor":"SessionConfiguration","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned previously, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Furthermore, the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the "},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a "},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"-related properties, named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned earlier, a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date."}]}],"style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration"},"references":{"atprotokit_icon.png":{"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/atprotokit_icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":"A technology icon representing the ATProtoKit framework.","identifier":"atprotokit_icon.png"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtoKit":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/atprotokit","title":"ATProtoKit","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ATProtoKit"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The base class that handles the main functionality of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ATProtoKit"},{"type":"text","text":" API library."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ATProtoKit","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SessionConfiguration/codeStream":{"kind":"symbol","required":true